symptoms: often accompanied by warning lights or error codes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Continuously Variable Transmission (CVT) can cause the vehicle to lose power, decelerate, or stall, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: often without warning; the vehicle may hesitate or jerk when shifting gears; the transmission may make unusual noises or produce a burning smell.

the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
